    Mia Stare6 months ago on Google
    5/5
    Great cafe. The prices are very reasonable- it's a three-minute walk from Majorelle Gardens but a bit further than the tourist cafes so it's not a rip-off tourist trap. Most of the customers were locals when we went. 
    Great cafe. The prices are very reasonable- it's a three-minute walk from Majorelle Gardens but a bit further than the tourist cafes so it's not a rip-off tourist trap. Most of the customers were locals when we went.
    The service was really good, best we've had so far in Marrakesh actually. The waitress quickly took our order and everything arrived very promptly.
    It has a mix of European and Moroccan food. We only had a dessert and juices so can't comment on mains.
    Would definitely recommend.
